HEADWORD: Infame
<hw>In*fame"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>infamare</ets>, fr. <ets>infamis</ets> infamous: cf. F.
<ets>infamer</ets>, It. <ets>infamare</ets>. See
<er>Infamous</er>.]</ety> <def>To defame; to make infamous.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Livia is <qex>infamed</qex> for the poisoning of her husband.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Infamize</ent>⟦br⟧
